# Cursor Rules for Space Trader Project

## Read first

- `README.md` — architecture and the four invariants (no magic, determinism,
  restartability, needs-consistency). Do not break them.
- `REVIEW.md` — why the first attempt failed; avoid repeating it.
- `PROGRESS.md` — roadmap. One task at a time, each with a scenario test.

## Hard rules

- **No hidden stabilizers.** Only production, consumption, and ship trades
  may change inventory or credits. Never add code that injects or "corrects"
  stock to keep the economy alive — if it doesn't balance, the balance
  numbers or trader behavior are wrong, and the fix belongs there.
- **Determinism.** All randomness goes through the seeded `Rng` (`src/rng.ts`).
  Same seed + same external events must produce a bit-identical `stateHash()`.
- **Production chain stays a DAG** with input-free roots (food, ore).
  `src/balance.test.ts` enforces this; keep it passing.
- **Every feature lands with a scenario test** in the spirit of
  `src/self-balance.test.ts`, proving the economy still self-balances.

## Code style

- TypeScript strict mode; never use `any`.
- Keep functions focused; descriptive names.
- Comments explain constraints and *why*, not what the next line does.

## Testing

- `npm test` runs type-check + vitest. Keep it green.
- Every crash fix gets a regression test.

## File layout

- `src/goods.ts` — goods catalog, production chain, role rates
- `src/market.ts` — price formation and trade execution
- `src/system.ts` — star system production/consumption tick
- `src/trader.ts` — NPC trader decisions
- `src/galaxy.ts` — deterministic galaxy generation
- `src/sim.ts` — orchestrator, external events, metrics
- `src/cli.ts` — headless demo (`npm run sim`)
